April, May and June 2020 payments can also be deferred for five months for (monthly payers). Note that lodgements are still required to be performed on time, and the exemption excludes VAT for imports.<\\\/p>\\n\\n\n\n<h2 class=\\\"uk-h3\\\">3. Household Businesses &amp; Individuals \\u2013 VAT and PIT Deferrals<\\\/h2>\\n\n\n<p>The annual VAT and PIT payments due for 2020 for household businesses and individuals can be deferred until 31 December 2020.<\\\/p>\\n\\n\n\n<h2 class=\\\"uk-h3\\\">4. Land Rental Deferrals<\\\/h2>\\n\n\n<p>Taxpayers with direct land lease contracts from the State can defer 2020 annual land rental payments for five months, from 31 May 2020.<\\\/p>\\n\\n\n\n<h2 class=\\\"uk-h3\\\">5. Applicable Taxpayers<\\\/h2>\\n\\n\n\n<p><strong>i) Those involved in production activities covering:<\\\/strong><\\\/p>\\n\n\n<ol type=\\\"a\\\">\\n    \n\n<li>agricultural, forestry and fisheries sectors<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>production and processing of food, textile &amp; garments, and footwear<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>production of wooden, metal, paper, plastic and rubber products<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>production of electronic products, computers and optical products<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>automobile manufacturing<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>construction sector<\\\/li>\\n<\\\/ol>\\n\\n\n\n<p><strong>ii) Those operating in service sectors covering:<\\\/strong><\\\/p>\\n\n\n<ol type=\\\"a\\\">\\n    \n\n<li>transport sector and associated supporting activities<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>accommodation and catering services<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>travel agents, tour businesses and support services related to tour promotion and organisation<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>training and education<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>medical and social assistance activities<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>real estate businesses<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>artists, recreational activities, sport activities, museums and cinemas<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>labour and employment services<\\\/li>\\n<\\\/ol>\\n\\n\n\n<p><strong>iii) Taxpayers engaged in the production of industrial products supporting the development of Vietnam and other key mechanical products (following previous guidelines released by the government on supporting industry development, and mechanical engineering development)<\\\/strong><\\\/p>\\n\\n\n\n<p><strong>iv) Small and micro enterprises defined by regulations of the law on supporting SMEs. The definitions include:<\\\/strong><\\\/p>\\n\\n\n\n<ul>\\n    \n\n<li>Enterprises in the fields of agriculture, forestry, fisheries, construction and industrial sectors with no more than 100 staff, and turnover no more than VND50 billion or total capital not more than VND20 billion<\\\/li>\\n    \n\n<li>Enterprises in the fields of commerce and services with no more than 50 staff, and turnover no more than VND100 billion or total capital not more than VND50 billion<\\\/li>\\n<\\\/ul>\\n\\n\n\n<p><strong>v) Credit institutions and foreign bank branches, for those affected by the COVID-19 epidemic, as prescribed by the State Bank of Vietnam<\\\/strong><\\\/p>\\n\\n\n\n<h2 class=\\\"uk-h3\\\">6. Implementation &amp; Access to Deferrals<\\\/h2>\\n\n\n<p>Taxpayers wishing to take advantage of the tax deferrals in this Decree using the form attached to this Decree, and which needs to be submitted no later than 30 July 2020. Submission can be made electronically or in paper form.<\\\/p>\\n\\n\n\n<p>The Decree took effect on 8 April 2020 when issued.<\\\/p>\\n\"}}]}]}]}],\"version\":\"1.22.8\"} --><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>News Vietnamese government issued decree providing tax relief to businesses due to COVID-19. On 8 April 2020, the Vietnam Government issued Decree 41\/2020\/ND-CP deferring certain payments for value added tax (\u201cVAT\u201d), corporate income tax (\u201cCIT\u201d), personal income tax (\u201cPIT\u201d) and government land rent for selected taxpayers, to support businesses in Vietnam impacted by COVID-19. Implementation [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","